(40, 6, 28, 42, 22, 35, 36, NULL, 'Provision and Preparation', 'This connection highlights the theme of reliance on God for provision in both passages. While Matthew emphasizes the carefree growth of lilies, Luke shifts to a call for preparedness, suggesting a balance between trust and practical action.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 29, 14, 9, 20, 22, 'Solomon in all his glory', 'Solomon''s Glory Comparison', 'This connection highlights the comparison of Solomon''s glory and wealth in both passages. Matthew emphasizes that even Solomon''s grandeur is surpassed by nature''s beauty, while 2 Chronicles details Solomon''s unmatched riches and splendor.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 29, 14, 9, 4, 6, 'Solomon in all his glory', 'Solomon''s Glory Comparison', 'This connection highlights the grandeur of Solomon as described in both passages. Matthew emphasizes that even Solomon''s glory is surpassed by nature, while 2 Chronicles details the splendor of his court and wisdom.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 29, 11, 10, 4, 7, 'Solomon in all his glory', 'Solomon''s Glory and Wisdom', 'Both passages emphasize the extraordinary splendor of Solomon. Matthew highlights that even Solomon''s glory is surpassed by nature''s beauty, while 1 Kings describes the awe inspired by Solomon''s wisdom and wealth.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 29, 54, 2, 9, 10, 'not arrayed like one of these', 'Contrast in Adornment', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of external appearance and its value. Matthew highlights that even Solomon''s glory does not compare to the natural beauty of creation, while 1 Timothy instructs women to focus on modesty rather than costly adornments.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 29, 60, 3, 2, 5, NULL, 'Contrast of Outer and Inner Beauty', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between outward appearance and inner character. Matthew highlights the glory of nature compared to Solomon''s splendor, while 1 Peter advises against focusing on external adornment, promoting a meek spirit instead.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 30, 40, 14, 31, 31, 'O ye of little faith', 'Connection of Little Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''O ye of little faith,'' highlighting a theme of doubt in God''s provision. This connection illustrates the struggle of faith in the face of uncertainty.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 30, 42, 12, 28, 28, 'O ye of little faith', 'Clothing of the Grass Connection', 'Both passages emphasize God''s provision for His creation, specifically mentioning how He clothes the grass of the field. The repetition of the phrase ''O ye of little faith'' highlights a shared theme of trust in God''s care.', 'parallel', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 30, 60, 1, 24, 24, 'grass of the field', 'Connection of Grass Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the transience of grass, illustrating the fleeting nature of life and human glory. Matthew highlights God''s provision for His creation, while Peter reflects on the impermanence of flesh and glory.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 30, 40, 8, 26, 26, 'O ye of little faith', 'Faith and Divine Provision', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of faith, specifically addressing those with ''little faith.'' In Matthew 6:30, the focus is on God''s provision for needs, while Matthew 8:26 highlights fear in the face of challenges, urging trust in God''s power.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 30, 59, 1, 10, 11, 'grass of the field', 'Connection of Grass Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the fleeting nature of grass, symbolizing the temporary state of life and material wealth. Matthew highlights God''s provision for the grass, while James reflects on the transience of the rich, comparing them to withering grass.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 30, 43, 20, 27, 27, 'O ye of little faith', 'Connection of Faith and Belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of faith in both passages. Matthew addresses those with ''little faith,'' while John encourages Thomas to be ''not faithless, but believing.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 30, 41, 4, 40, 40, 'O ye of little faith', 'Connection of Faith and Fear', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of faith, with Matthew highlighting the lack of faith in God''s provision and Mark addressing fear stemming from a lack of faith. This connection highlights the importance of trusting in God''s care amidst challenges.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 31, 60, 5, 7, 7, 'What shall we eat? or, What shall we drink? or, Wherewithal shall we be clothed?', 'Concern for Daily Needs', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of not worrying about daily needs. Matthew 6:31 addresses concerns about food and clothing, while 1 Peter 5:7 encourages casting all cares upon God, who cares for us.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 31, 42, 12, 29, 29, 'What shall we eat? or, What shall we drink?', 'Concern for Daily Needs', 'Both passages emphasize not worrying about daily necessities such as food and drink. They encourage a mindset free from anxiety regarding material needs.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 31, 40, 4, 4, 4, 'What shall we eat? or, What shall we drink?', 'Dependence on God''s Provision', 'This connection highlights the theme of reliance on God for sustenance. Both passages emphasize that life is not solely about physical needs, such as food and drink, but also about spiritual nourishment from God''s word.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 31, 19, 55, 22, 22, 'What shall we eat? or, What shall we drink? or, Wherewithal shall we be clothed?', 'Trusting God for Provision', 'Both passages emphasize reliance on God for sustenance and support. Matthew 6:31 addresses concerns about basic needs, while Psalms 55:22 encourages casting burdens on the Lord for sustenance.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 31, 40, 15, 33, 33, 'What shall we eat?', 'Concern for Basic Needs', 'Both passages emphasize the disciples'' anxiety about food and sustenance. In Matthew 6:31, Jesus instructs not to worry about what to eat, while in Matthew 15:33, the disciples express concern about feeding a multitude in the wilderness.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 31, 19, 37, 3, 3, 'What shall we eat? or, What shall we drink? or, Wherewithal shall we be clothed?', 'Trust and Provision', 'Both passages emphasize reliance on God for sustenance and security. Matthew 6:31 speaks to not worrying about basic needs, while Psalms 37:3 encourages trust in the Lord for provision.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 31, 14, 25, 9, 9, 'What shall we eat? or, What shall we drink? or, Wherewithal shall we be clothed?', 'Provision and Trust in God', 'This connection highlights the theme of reliance on God for provision. Both passages emphasize concerns about material needs, with Matthew urging not to worry about food and clothing, while Amaziah questions his financial commitment, receiving reassurance that God can provide abundantly.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 32, 40, 6, 8, 8, NULL, 'God''s Knowledge of Our Needs', 'Both passages emphasize that God knows our needs before we ask or seek them. This connection highlights the assurance believers have in God''s awareness and provision.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 32, 42, 12, 30, 30, 'for your heavenly Father knoweth that ye have need of all these things', 'Connection of Divine Provision', 'Both passages emphasize that the Father knows the needs of His followers. They highlight a common theme of reliance on God for provision, contrasting it with the pursuits of the Gentiles and nations.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 32, 49, 4, 17, 17, 'Gentiles seek', 'Gentiles and Their Walk', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the Gentiles'' pursuits and the believers'' reliance on God. Both passages emphasize the different ways of living, with Matthew noting the Gentiles'' focus on material needs and Ephesians urging believers not to walk as the Gentiles do.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 32, 42, 11, 11, 13, 'your heavenly Father knoweth that ye have need of all these things', 'Provision by the Heavenly Father', 'Both passages emphasize the care of the heavenly Father for His children. Matthew highlights that the Father knows our needs, while Luke illustrates that He gives good gifts, including the Holy Spirit, to those who ask.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 32, 19, 17, 14, 14, 'need of all these things', 'Provision and Human Pursuits', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between earthly pursuits and divine provision. Matthew highlights that God knows our needs, while Psalms reflects on those who seek their portion in this life.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 32, 40, 20, 25, 26, 'the Gentiles seek', 'Gentile Authority and Divine Provision', 'This connection highlights the contrast between Gentile behavior and the values of Jesus'' followers. Both passages emphasize that while Gentiles seek material needs, true greatness in the kingdom is found in serving others.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 32, 52, 4, 5, 5, 'the Gentiles', 'Gentiles Seeking Knowledge of God', 'Both passages emphasize the behavior of the Gentiles in relation to their understanding of God. Matthew highlights that Gentiles seek material needs, while 1 Thessalonians contrasts this with the Gentiles who do not know God, suggesting a lack of spiritual awareness.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 33, 14, 31, 20, 21, NULL, 'Seeking God and Prosperity', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of seeking God wholeheartedly. Matthew 6:33 encourages prioritizing God''s kingdom, while 2 Chronicles 31:20-21 describes Hezekiah''s dedication to seeking God, resulting in prosperity.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 33, 19, 34, 9, 10, NULL, 'Seeking God and Provision', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of seeking the Lord and promise that those who do will lack nothing. Matthew 6:33''s call to seek the kingdom aligns with Psalms 34:10''s assurance that those who seek the Lord shall not want any good thing.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 33, 19, 37, 3, 3, 'seek ye first the kingdom of God', 'Seeking God and Trusting Him', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prioritizing one''s relationship with God. Matthew 6:33 encourages seeking God''s kingdom first, while Psalms 37:3 highlights trusting in the Lord and doing good, suggesting that such actions lead to provision.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
